  "response": "The Information Sciences Institute (ISI) at the University of Southern California (USC) has a strong reputation in the field of computer science. It is well-known for its contributions to research and development in areas such as artificial intelligence, networking and cybersecurity, natural language processing, and microelectronics.\n\nISI has a history of pioneering work, including significant contributions to the development of the internet, cybersecurity, and advanced AI technologies. It is highly regarded for its influential research outputs, collaboration with government agencies, and its role in advancing fundamental and applied research in computer science and related fields.\n\nThe institute attracts top-tier researchers and has been involved in numerous high-impact projects, making it a respected entity within the academic and professional communities in computer science.",
